\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Regularization path. As community structure $\eta $ increases (green, left axis), the within-group edge share rises from uniform mixing ($1/K = 0.25$) toward 1. ODE posterior bias (red, right axis) decreases monotonically and convexly. At $\eta = 0$ the network is approximately Erd\H {o}s--R\'enyi and bias is near zero; at $\eta = 3$ bias reaches $-0.48$.}}{6}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:reg_path}{{3}{6}{Regularization path. As community structure $\eta $ increases (green, left axis), the within-group edge share rises from uniform mixing ($1/K = 0.25$) toward 1. ODE posterior bias (red, right axis) decreases monotonically and convexly. At $\eta = 0$ the network is approximately Erd\H {o}s--R\'enyi and bias is near zero; at $\eta = 3$ bias reaches $-0.48$}{figure.3}{}}
